This paper deals with the problem of data exchange among wireless nodes, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The problem is also related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and social networks (cs.SI) since the nodes need to cooperate with each other to exchange data. Finally, the use of algorithms and simulations to solve the problem suggests a connection to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
